sub_title: Material Chemist | TEM, Nanomaterials Science, Utrecht University | Inorganic chemistry | Heterogeneous Catalysis
summary:
My expertise lies in nanomaterials science, material chemistry, heterogeneous catalysis, and physical chemistry, which I apply to conduct research. Throughout my academic journey, I have gained valuable experience in developing and optimizing synthesis methods, characterizing nanomaterials, and analyzing data using Python.

I am skilled in various analytical techniques, including TEM, ED, TEM-EDX, SEM, Optical Microscopy, TPR, XRD, TGA, TPD, and N2 physisorption. I have contributed to multiple projects, such as spray drying of FCC catalysts for plastic recycling, nickel phyllosilicate nanotubes, and ion conductance in carbon porous electrodes.

My passion lies in advancing the understanding and application of nanomaterials and catalysis to address environmental and industrial challenges. I am eager to contribute my knowledge and skills to make a positive impact in these fields.
